product_name: e.l.f. CosmeticsPower Grip Dewy Setting Spray
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVegane.l.f. Cosmetics' shockingly fine bi-phase Power Grip Dewy Setting Spray features a water-based phase and moisturizing oil-based phase. Boosted with 5% aloe, plus hyaluronic acid, squalene, and green tea seed oil. Shake to activate the power of both phases for dewy, long-lasting makeup looks.

reviews.headline: Was good at first...until I got to the end...
reviews.comments: I really did like this setting spray at first! I have combination acne-prone skin to start. Didn't break me out. However, when I got to the end, my face felt incredibly greasy after use. I have no idea if this is the same for others.

reviews.headline: Not seeing any results besides oil
reviews.comments: Although I was very confident in this setting spray, I didnt see a result. My makeup ended up fading away. I thought it was because I didnt shake the product, when I did, it only made my skin oily and didn't set my makeup.

reviews.headline: LOVELY
reviews.comments: The mist isn't as watery more oily and light weight. Helps set my makeup very well, happy with it.

reviews.headline: Elf Setting Mist
reviews.comments: It sprays out very fine, too fine. It makes my makeup slide around. It goes on nicely, but after a few minutes, it gets extremely greasy and oily. I definitely prefer the Dewy Coconut one.

reviews.headline: I gave it my best shot
reviews.comments: I wanted to go through an entire bottle of this before I wrote a review just to make sure my opinion was solidified. I really wanted to love this. I was looking for an affordable dewy setting spray. After using all of it, I can say I have never felt like it gave a "dewy" effect. I actually felt like it didn't do much of anything at all. The mist felt way too fine to really set my makeup. I found myself using so much of it just to feel as though I had a sufficient amount of producg on my face. My makeup had little to no staying power with it. Maybe it's just my skin type or the other products I was using? Feeling really frustrated, I ended up buying a more expensive dewy setting spray and it did everything for me that I hoped this product would do based on the advertisements. For an affordable product, its something, and something is better than nothing. But certainly not my daily driver.

reviews.headline: Broken
reviews.comments: The nozzle was broken when I received it, and every time I use it, it drips down my hand.

reviews.headline: Elf Dewy Setting Spray
reviews.comments: Tried this expecting it to be decent but not the best. It made my makeup last for about 5 hours and then it wore of. Definitely not sweat or transfer proof and not for oily skin. Good for lighter makeup and dry skin.

reviews.headline: LOVE
reviews.comments: I loveeee this setting spray. Im on bottle #3 ans it's definitely a holy grail for me.

reviews.headline: Smells like a lab accident
reviews.comments: The odor of the spray is so harsh. Its like melting plastic mixed with antiseptic. I could forgive it if the smell didnt last so lony—it doesnt go away for at least a couple of minutes. I love the grippy gel primer from this collection and had high hopes.

reviews.headline: It's ok
reviews.comments: I liked it at first, i think my soft glam satin was doing most of the work to be honest. Now it leaves these oily wet droplets on my face. Ive always shaken it up before using but now its just weird and i dont use it anymore. I should throw it away. The kicker is im only like half way through it so even though it was good and i was planning on sticking with it i cant anymore

reviews.headline: 50%of work done
reviews.comments: I shook the container as instructed and sprayed it on my face several times because I wanted it to work,it didn't set my makeup,it only left a shine and big liquid droplets on my face every time I tried again. I had to return it.

reviews.headline: Spray nozzle
reviews.comments: I love this product but the only down side for me is the spray nozzle. I feel like its kinda hard to press down. And if I try to spray a bit faster product leaks from it.

reviews.headline: not good product
reviews.comments: the setting spray doesnt dry, seperates makeup, and makes your face oily. will not be buying again.

reviews.headline: I love this product!!
reviews.comments: Keeps my makeup looking amazing all day!!!

reviews.headline: Definitely would use again
reviews.comments: Its a very fine mist but works very well!

reviews.headline: Not for hot weather
reviews.comments: I always end up looking greasy when I use this setting spray. I would recommend using it during winter for when your skin get dried out.

reviews.headline: no
reviews.comments: the spray is the weirdest thing ever it literally goes in the air and at the floor everywhere but my face??? the mist is so fine and feel really nice (the few drops that gets on my face at least) so im annoyed that the spray is bad. i expected it to be a little more dewy but its okay. i prefer my milani one, tbis one doesnt last as good

reviews.headline: Not good for acne prone skin
reviews.comments: It definitely sets makeup like a dream but only for an hour or so, also clogged my pores

reviews.headline: It rivals Urban Decay's All-nighter.
reviews.comments: If you're looking for a setting spray that lasts like all-nighter but comes with a cheaper price tag, this is it. I tested it out in 97 degree weather and its a winner!

reviews.headline: Love the spray
reviews.comments:
Really has helped with my makeup looking fresh and keeps
My face from shining!

faceoff_positive.comments: [This review was collected as part of a TopBoxCircle marketing promotion.] I love it! It has a nice packaging, amazing coverage and finish once applied on the skin with a nice scent. It is truly a must have for summer, it has natural ingredients and a quality spray nozzle. I love this setting spray, it pairs really well with the Power Grip foundation and makes your makeup stay in place all day. It makes you look radiant but not greasy. I have very oily skin, I don't usually go for radiant finishes but this one really surprised me unlike other products I have used. This spray helped me keep the oil at bay exceeding my expectations. This setting spray kept my makeup in place for hours. It felt great as it absorbed into my skin. I have always loved ELF products, the price is great, the packaging is easy and simple. There is no scent I can make out. Easy spray, soothing and smooth. If you want that radiant look, this is definitely the setting spray for you. You will feel extremely confident and sensual. I managed to keep my makeup looking flawless all day. It's lovely and lightweight, some sprays make your face feel very wet but this one is lovely and very well received... (see photo after application).
faceoff_positive.headline: Awesome.

faceoff_negative.comments:
I've been using urban decay dewy setting spray for ages , and I thought I'd try this as it's a fraction of the cost and is supposed to deliver similar results.

It's just ok, but great for the price point , I suppose . The fine mist , at least for me , is too fine ; I can't tell if I have adequate coverage or not. I also find that it doesn't blur imperfections as well as urban decay does , and on aging skin that's especially important. The smell is also unpleasant to me ..best I can describe it is a wet band-aid .

All that said , the staying power is very impressive and on par with the more expensive sprays , and I like the natural ingredients.

I still prefer the more expensive brand , but this one will do if needed.
faceoff_negative.headline: Close , but not quite .
